    "max_investigation_loops": 4,
    "model_response": "ROOT_CAUSE: The checkout deployment is CPU-saturated. All three checkout pods ({{POD}}, {{POD2}}, {{POD3}}) are running at their 1000m CPU limit (avg rate 0.97 cores/sec vs 0.5 target) and are being CFS-throttled (throttle ratio 0.86), which queues requests and drives checkout p99 to 1.48s. There is insufficient capacity (CPU) for current request volume — the fix is to scale the deployment to more replicas (or raise CPU limits).\nROOT_CAUSE_CATEGORY: saturation\nVALIDATED_CLAIMS:\n- avg(rate(container_cpu_usage_seconds_total)) = 0.97 cores/sec, above the 0.5 SLO, sustained 2m+ [evidence: prometheus_metrics]\n- All checkout containers are at the 1000m CPU limit and CFS-throttled (throttled ratio ~0.86) [evidence: k8s_pods]\n- CPUThrottlingHigh events firing on {{POD}} and {{POD2}} [evidence: k8s_events]\n- Logs show 'CPU pegged on checkout workers', request queue depth 312, and a timeout that is CPU-bound with no downstream call in flight [evidence: k8s_pod_logs]\n- Deployment is fully Available/Progressing with 3/3 ready replicas, so capacity (not health) is the constraint [evidence: k8s_deployments]\nNON_VALIDATED_CLAIMS:\n- Exact incoming RPS increase is not directly measured; capacity shortfall is inferred from saturation + throttling\nCAUSAL_CHAIN:\n- Request volume exceeds the aggregate CPU headroom of 3 checkout replicas\n- Each pod hits its 1000m CPU limit and the kernel CFS-throttles it (ratio ~0.86)\n- Throttled workers cannot keep up; request queue grows (depth 312) and handler time rises to ~1.48s p99\n- Requests exceed the 2000ms timeout and fail; HighCPUUsage + ContainerCPUThrottled alerts fire\n- Remediation: add CPU capacity by scaling checkout replicas so per-pod CPU drops below the 0.5 SLO and throttling clears"
  },
  "remediation": {
    "fix_tool": "scale_deployment",
    "canonical_fix": "kubectl delete stresschaos -n chaos-mesh cpu-checkout; kubectl scale deployment/checkout -n rlvr-target --replicas=5",
    "trust_tier": "approval",
    "primary_metric": "rate(container_cpu_usage_seconds_total[1m])",
